          "date": "2018-04-10 20:02:34.000000000",
          "tz": 0
        },
        "subject": "LU-10560 libcfs: Use kernel_write when appropriate",
        "message": "LU-10560 libcfs: Use kernel_write when appropriate\n\nChanges in the upstream kernel might have removed\nvfs_write() in favor of kernel_write().\n\nUnfortunately, the kernel_write() was initially exported\nwith an API that is not plug compatible with vfs_write()\n\nThe ring down is:\n- kernel_write new API\n- vfs_write\n\nLustre-change: https://review.whamcloud.com/31154\nLustre-commit: b9a32054600a8d63948cced361191aa6ae7ea8f2\n\nChange-Id: I67f73786308561dc42b06d51c26bfb94021b7589\nSigned-off-by: Mike Marciniszyn <mike.marciniszyn@intel.com>\nReviewed-by: James Simmons <uja.ornl@yahoo.com>\nReviewed-by: Dmitry Eremin <dmitry.eremin@intel.com>\nReviewed-by: John L. Hammond <john.hammond@intel.com>\nSigned-off-by: Minh Diep <minh.diep@intel.com>\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/b2_10"
    }
